JOHANNESBURG – Security officers at the OR Tambo International Airport on Friday busted women bound for Seychelles Island with two bricks of cocaine weighing 1,040 kilograms, the Airports company said. “The attention of the security team at the central search point of Terminal A was drawn to a passenger with what appeared to be an unusual body shape,” said Airport spokesperson, Leigh Gunkel-Keuler. READ: Alleged drug traffickers nabbed at OR Tambo “The security team requested a private search in terms of the legal procedures. During the search, security staff discovered two bricks containing cocaine concealed by seven additional brassieres,” says Gunkel-Keuler.   The woman has since been handed over to members of the SAPS. eNCA